diamonds %>%
  group_by(color) %>% 
  summarize(AveSize = mean(carat)) %>% 
  arrange(-AveSize)
## # A tibble: 7  2
##   color   AveSize
##   <ord>     <dbl>
## 1     J 1.1621368
## 2     I 1.0269273
## 3     H 0.9117991
## 4     G 0.7711902
## 5     F 0.7365385
## 6     E 0.6578667
## 7     D 0.6577948

Based on this result, we see that color J is the largest on average. J represents the worst quality of color.

diamonds %>%
  group_by(clarity) %>%
  mutate(TpC = table/carat) %>%
  summarize(TpCAve = mean(TpC)) %>%
  arrange(-TpCAve) %>% 
  head(1)
## # A tibble: 1  2
##   clarity   TpCAve
##     <ord>    <dbl>
## 1    VVS1 141.4822

Well the clarity VVS1 has the highest average table per carat.
